		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Flipping is one table lookup per byte. And if you're using <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=136825#p136825" class="postlink">real-time sprite scaling</a>, you get flipping for free because you can bake flipping into a second set of scaling tables. Or is that sort of lookup hard on Z80?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


